<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>50862</id>
    <title>FcgidWrapper in &lt;Directory&gt; blocks</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">I am using mod_fcgid 2.3.6, and I wanted to setup two kind of fcgid apps based on the documentroot, with this config:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">&lt;Directory /web/apps1&gt;
  AddHandler fcgid-script .</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">app
  FcgidWrapper "/usr/local/app1/wrapper.sh" .</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">app
&lt;/Directory&gt;
&lt;Directory /web/apps2&gt;
  AddHandler fcgid-script .</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">app
  FcgidWrapper "/usr/local/app2/wrapper.sh" .</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">app
&lt;/Directory&gt;</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">But when starting Apache I get:
FcgidWrapper not allowed here</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">I dont understand, if its is possible to bind a specific wrapper to a &lt;Location&gt; block, why is it not possible to bind it to a &lt;Directory&gt; ?</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Please add this feature to the module, it would help a lot.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
